<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;Last point to make tonight - you took my Clinton statement out of context. Go back and reread it. In context, you will see that when I state I would answer the questions if asked, I was referring to a congressional hearing. Not a public message board.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Your point is well taken. Under oath you are saying that you would in fact answer the question. I believe we are talking past each other on this point after reviewing the previous posts. So let me clear up my end. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I am saying that you found the questions I asked rude and insulting. I asked if you would really answer them before a congressional hearing, and doubted you would based upon your responses (I believe the distinction you make between answering such questions in a public forum or under oath really trivializes the nature of the point I was making: such questions are improper no matter where asked and do not deserve an answer). I also pointed out that such questions being asked of the President is equally as rude and should not have been asked to begin with. Dirty politics.<br>
